\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Conceptual overview of towing-based cooperation on a 1D corridor (positions $0$--$100$\,m). Dashed gray segments denote self-driving portions (PV uses own propulsion); solid colored segments denote towed travel (PV propulsion offset by AV). AVs $A_1$ and $A_2$ each have towing capacity\nonbreakingspace 2. $T2$ is towed by $A_1$ over $[20,60]$, self-drives over $[60,70]$, and is handed off to $A_2$ over $[70,90]$ -- an instance of \emph  {multi-segment matching}.}}{2}{figure.caption.5}\protected@file@percent }
